                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           British aid for Bihar reforms
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Patna, Nov. 18: Chief minister Nitish Kumar and the British governments secretary of state for international development, Douglas Alexander, today jointly launched the Bihar administrative reforms mission, which aims to improve the system of governance in the state.        
	The UK department for international development (DFID) will support the mission for which it will provide Rs 150 crore in over six years (2008-14).        
	Nitish said: Effective delivery of basic social services to our people cannot be ensured unless the institutions that are charged with these functions are made accountable to the people themselves.        
	Reminding that he had given governance top priority when he assumed power, Nitish enumerated the measures his government had taken to ensure good governance.         
	Janata ke darbar mein mukhyamantri (CM in peoples court) and Jankari, a call centre related to right to information that handles around 2,000 applications from people a month, are among the initiatives that the government had undertaken to stay directly in touch with people, he said.        
	Alexander said that the reforms were important not for its own sake but for the citizens and better services to them.         
	The DFID support will help tackle problems in the back office functions of the government  in administration, training, posting and performance management, he said.        
	Alexander said: The programme will improve the system by bringing more functions online, introducing a new staffing structure across the government and modernising commercial tax collection system to improve the states revenue  all vital foundation for Bihars prosperity.                                                                                                                                                                          
